Lafia – Umaru Tanko Al-Makura, Nasarawa State governor, on Thursday charged the newly appointed Nasarawa State Chairman of Board of Internally Generated Revenue to increase the state’s revenue to N12  billion annually. Al-Makura gave the charged at Government House, Lafia, while inaugurating the newly appointed Nasarawa State Internal Revenue Service Board in Lafia, the state capital. In his keynote address shortly after the inauguration, the governor said government could not thrive without adequate revenue generation that prompted government decision to properly constituted management to support government towards the realisation of the desired revenue target. “We have decided to peg an annual revenue target of N12 billion in the beginning and N20 billion in the long run. “I urge you to synergise with appropriate Ministries, Departments and Agencies (MDAs) such as Ministries of Lands and Physical Planning, Commerce, Industry and Co-operatives, Agriculture, Urban Development Board and other agencies to explore available options for revenue generation. “It became imperative for government to take deliberate steps to address the situation through the reconstitution of the Board of the State Revenue Service in line with the enabling law. He advised the board chairman to work hand-in-hand with the State Appointed Revenue Generation Consultants, Cyber1 Systems Network Limited and others in pursuing all possible claims, dues charges, revenue accruals and recover same for the benefit of the state. He however assured the board of Government support and political will towards the attainment of the objectives of the organisation. 1 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE.  100% Natural Solution To Premature Ejaculation, Weak Erection, Watery Sperm, Other Sexual Dysfunctions And Last More Than 30 Minutes During Sex.